The article discusses the importance of the National Guard and Reserve members in the United States military and acknowledges the support they receive from their employers. It emphasizes the sacrifices made by these service members and their contributions to both the military and their communities. The article also highlights the efforts of patriotic employers who offer leave policies and maintain benefits for deployed service members and their families. President Biden proclaims August 20 to August 26 as National Employer Support of the Guard and Reserve Week, calling upon Americans to honor and appreciate these service members and their employers. The article concludes with President Biden's signature and date.